      "domain": "docs.apify.com",
      "page_title": "Apify Documentation",
      "content": "Learn how to put the web to work.\nThe full reference of the Apify platform.\nDevelop, run, and share web scraping and automation tools in the cloud.\nStore files and results of your web scraping jobs, and export it to various formats.\nAvoid blocking by smartly rotating datacenter and residential IP addresses.\nAutomatically start Actors and saved tasks at specific times.\nConnect Actors with your favorite web apps and cloud services.\nCheck the performance of your Actors, validate data quality, and receive alerts.\nShare Actors with other people, manage your organizations and permissions.\nLearn about Apify platform security and data protection.\nDiscover and use Actors with AI agents and LLMs via Apify MCP server.\nInteract with the Apify platform from your applications.\nSoftware toolkits for developing new Actors.\nControl the Apify platform from terminal or shell scripts.\nFree practical courses on web scraping and the Apify platform. Go from beginner to expert, all in one place.\nLearn the basics of web scraping and how to develop your own scraper.\nLearn the basics of the Apify platform and how to use it for your scraping projects.\nLearn how to efficiently extract data from web pages' APIs.\nUnderstand the various anti-scraping measures and how to avoid them.\nLearn how to extract data from more complicated websites.\nLearn how to easily move your existing projects to the Apify platform.\nToolkit for generating and injecting realistic browser fingerprints into Playwright and Puppeteer.\nNode.js proxy server with SSL, authentication, and upstream proxy chaining.\nOpen specification for Actors, the serverless microapps at the core of the Apify platform.\nCreate new web scraping projects using ready-made templates for various programming languages and scraping libraries.",
